<p class="p">A spatial pattern detection technique was used to analyse clusters of high and low values of persistence. This analysis allowed to identify areas that experience a significantly higher level of persistence to coastal flooding due to SLR in the LPBR, and to assess that these values were not random events. The Getis–Ord G
 <sub class="sub">i</sub>* statistic [
 <xref rid="pone.0162637.ref056" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">56</xref>] was used to assess such hot spots of resilience at the LPBR. 
